    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to material that contains a greater length of grain boundaries than a coarse-grained material. Grain boundaries restrict slip transmission to neighboring grains. A fine-grain material has a higher tensile strength and is thus harder than a coarse-grained material.</Note_Text>
